context: But it were al to longe for to devyse
And she was to hym trewe for everemoore
For joye of this so loude and heighe withalle
But on a day wel armed brighte and shene
Somme seyde he looked grymme and he wolde fighte
And now swetnesse semeth more swete
And shortly deere herte and al my knyght
Yet made he tho as fresshe a countenaunce
Myn housbonde hath longe asses erys two
A trewe wight and a theef thenken nat oon
Saugh he which is longe to telle
I knowe yow for a trewe wyf dame Alys
But myghte me so faire a grace falle
Now by my trouthe brother deere seyde he
But thilke tale is al to longe to telle
Is thorugh a goter by a pryve wente
For al to longe it were for to dwelle
For Goddes love as chees a newe requeste
In this matere bothe fremde and tame
With hym ther was dwellynge a poure scoler
Be the werkes never so queynte
That yow ne liketh for youre heighe prudence
It was not wele he dwelte so
For more clere entendement
Ther nas but hevynesse and muche sorwe
Had as moche debonairte
